The Biden-Harris Administration has announced that public tours of the White House will begin on April 15, 2022. The tours will be available on Fridays and Saturdays from 8:00 AM to 12:30 PM, excluding Federal holidays. The tours are free of charge. Tour requests must be submitted through a Member of Congress and their Congressional Tour Coordinator, and must be made 21 to 90 days in advance. The White House will monitor the COVID-19 situation and may adjust tour availability based on health guidance. Face masks will be available for those who choose to wear them. Information about other springtime events at the White House will be released soon.